Iran is going to maintain the right and the ability to enrich uranium. And Israel is never going to accept that. The lobby is never going to accept that.

123
00:25:20.150 --> 00:25:26.799
[Guest] 而且更广泛地说，这个国家里那些在政策圈影响力很大的新保守主义者，也永远不会接受。
And the neoconservatives more generally in this country who are very powerful in policy circles are never going to accept.

124
00:25:26.771 --> 00:25:43.571
[Guest] 所以，你知道，我们只会没完没了地就 Iran 的核能力跟他们争论，威胁他们，诸如此类。顺便说一句，如果你们在核问题上达不成一项有实质意义的协议，
So, you know, we're just going to go on and on arguing with the Iranians about their nuclear capability, threatening them and so forth and so on. And by the way, if you don't get a meaningful agreement on the nuclear issue,

125
00:25:43.721 --> 00:25:55.372
[Guest] 那我们就会面临一种可能性：Israel 可能会动用核武器来对付 Iran，解决这个问题。所以这里的未来是——
then we're going to run into the possibility that the Israelis may use nuclear weapons against Iran to deal with that problem. So the future here is.

126
00:25:55.284 --> 00:26:02.634
[Guest] 很黯淡。顺便说一句，Europe 的未来也很黯淡。East Asia 的未来也一样黯淡。
is bleak. And by the way, the future is bleak in Europe as well. The future in East Asia is bleak as well.

127
00:26:03.034 --> 00:26:19.483
[Guest] 我们把事情彻底搞砸了。当然，这不只是 Trump 政府政策造成的结果，尽管这场 Iran 战争对此推波助澜很大，但 Ukraine 的整场灾难也一直没完没了地持续着。
We have made a complete hash of things. Of course, it's not only the result of the Trump administration's policies, although this Iran war has contributed greatly to that, but the whole disaster in Ukraine just goes on and on and on.

128
00:26:19.933 --> 00:26:31.534
[Guest] 而这将在可预见的未来带来极其严重的负面战略后果。正如我之前指出的那样，这些后果和 Gulf 正在发生的事情是密不可分地纠缠在一起的。
And that is going to have serious serious negative strategic consequences for as far as the eye can see that, as I pointed out before, are inextricably bound up with what's going on in the Gulf.

129
00:26:31.733 --> 00:26:42.584
[Guest] 然后，这还先不谈整个东亚问题。东亚在很多方面其实是最危险的地区，因为美国在那里面对的是一个同级别的竞争对手。
And then this, you know, leaves aside the whole question of East Asia, which is in many ways the most dangerous area of all because that's where the United States faces a peer competitor.

130
00:26:43.183 --> 00:26:52.794
[Guest] 一想到如果东亚爆发危机会怎么样，我就不寒而栗。我希望 Trump 能和 Xi Jinping 合作，确保那种情况不会发生。不过你得记住，
I shudder to think what would happen if we had a crisis in East Asia. I hope Trump can work with Xi Jinping to make sure that that that doesn't happen. But you want to remember,

131
00:26:52.943 --> 00:27:10.243
[Guest] 现在有两场重大战争正在进行，一场在海湾地区，另一场在欧洲，而东亚还没有战争。但如果真有的话，我们可就真的陷入大麻烦了。谢天谢地，我们现在还没有这个问题。也希望，
we have two major wars taking place, one in the Gulf and the other in Europe, and we don't have a war in East Asia. But if we did, we would be in the really deep kimchi. And thankfully, we don't have that problem. And hopefully,

132
00:27:10.394 --> 00:27:15.594
[Guest] President Trump 能和 Xi 商量出个办法，避免那种情况发生。
President Trump can work something out with Xi so that that doesn't happen.

133
00:27:16.180 --> 00:27:32.480
[Host] President Trump 能和 President Putin 谈出什么结果？我的意思是，Putin 自己是不是也有他的难题？你有没有感觉到，俄罗斯精英、Kremlin 官员以及普通俄罗斯人，对这场已经打了四年的战争都开始不耐烦了？
What can President Trump work out with President Putin? I mean, and does Putin have his own issues? Do you sense impatience on the part of Russian elites, Kremlin officials and average Russians with a four year war now?

134
00:27:33.203 --> 00:27:34.953
[Guest] 对，这一点毫无疑问。
Yeah, there's no question about that.

135
00:27:35.003 --> 00:28:01.953
[Guest] 我一直在想一种可能性，就是俄罗斯人自己某个时候可能会动用核武器。很明显，欧洲人正在竭尽所能帮助乌克兰人，而乌克兰人现在也越来越擅长打击俄罗斯境内的目标。最终的结果就是，俄罗斯的外交政策精英，甚至连……
I've been thinking about the possibility that Russians, the Russians themselves might use nuclear weapons at some point. It's quite clear that the Europeans are doing everything they can to help the Ukrainians and the Ukrainians are getting quite effective at hitting targets inside of Russia. And the end result is Russian foreign policy elites and even the...

136
00:28:01.748 --> 00:28:18.402
[Guest] 甚至连普通民众，都开始急着想把这场战争了结掉。他们正在给 President Putin 施加巨大压力，要他结束这场战争，但这并不容易。我的意思是，即便俄罗斯人占领了越来越多的领土，
Even the public are getting antsy about settling this war. They're putting great pressure on President Putin to put an end to it, and it's not easy to do that. I mean, even as the Russians capture more and more territory,

137
00:28:18.652 --> 00:28:31.902
[Guest] 事实是，乌克兰人靠着这些无人机，以及他们从欧洲、甚至美国得到的各种援助，已经能够打击俄罗斯境内的目标了。问题在于，俄罗斯人会如何回应？
the fact is that the Ukrainians with all these drones and all the help they're getting from Europe and even the United States are able to attack targets in Russia. And the question is, what will the Russians do in response?

138
00:28:32.102 --> 00:28:44.279
[Guest] 还有一位非常知名的战略家，我跟他其实还算熟，Sergei Karaganov，长期以来一直在主张，俄罗斯必须结束这种局面。
And there's this very prominent strategist who I actually know reasonably well, Sergei Karaganov, who has been making the argument for a long time. long time that the Russians have to put an end to this.

139
00:28:44.380 --> 00:28:50.329
[Guest] 而唯一能做到这一点的办法，就是动用核武器，不是发动一场全面的热核战争，
And the only way you can do that is to use nuclear weapons, not start a general thermonuclear war,

140
00:28:50.480 --> 00:29:10.329
[Guest] 而是以一种示范性的方式对西方使用核武器，向西方发出信号：够了。如果他们继续支持乌克兰，并允许乌克兰摧毁俄罗斯的基础设施，那么俄罗斯接下来就会升级。
but use nuclear weapons against the West in a demonstrative way to signal to the West that enough is enough. And if they continue to support Ukraine and allow Ukraine to destroy Russian infrastructure, then what the Russians will do is they'll go up.

141
00:29:10.099 --> 00:29:22.950
[Guest] 把核升级的阶梯往上推。Karaganov 认为，一旦对西方使用几枚核武器，他们就会清清楚楚地明白这个信号，也就会停止支持乌克兰。
blow up the nuclear escalation ladder. And Kara Ganov argues that once you use a few nuclear weapons against the West, they will get the message loudly and clearly, and they will cease and desist from supporting Ukraine.

142
00:29:23.349 --> 00:29:28.849
[Guest] 但这里的关键点是，你不能把俄罗斯逼到绝境。
But the key point here is you don't want to put the Russians in a desperate situation.

143
00:29:29.849 --> 00:29:45.422
[Guest] 当然，欧洲现在恰恰就是在这么做。就像我之前说的，Sergey Lavrov 在 4 月 24 日发表了一场非常重要、非常重要的讲话，我觉得大家很值得回头去看看那场讲话。
And of course, that's exactly what Europe is trying to do. As I was saying before, Sergey Lavrov gave a very important very important speech on April 24th, and it would be well worth people's while to go back and look at that speech.

144
00:29:45.571 --> 00:30:00.349
[Guest] 但 Lavrov 说得非常明确，他认为——当然，这反映的是俄罗斯的视角——西方已经对俄罗斯宣战了。他认为，俄罗斯正在与西方交战。
But Lavrov makes it very clear that he believes, and of course he's reflecting a Russian perspective on this, that the West has declared war against Russia. He believes that Russia is at war with Russia. the West.

145
00:30:00.650 --> 00:30:19.355
[Guest] 而且他认为，Russia 不只是在 Ukraine 境内和 Ukraine 作战。Russia 其实也是在和 Europe 对抗。他说得非常明确：他相信 Europeans 的目标，是要在战略上战胜 Russia。
And he believes that Russia's just not fighting Ukraine inside of Ukraine. Russia is also fighting against Europe. And he says very clearly that he believes that the Europeans are out to To achieve a strategic victory against Russia.

146
00:30:19.455 --> 00:30:31.655
[Guest] 而他这番话的基本意思是，Europeans——当然，这其实也指整个 West，他自己用的也是 the West 这个说法——是想把 Russians 从大国行列里打出去。
And what he basically is saying is that the Europeans, and of course this means the West in general, and he uses the term the West, wants to knock the Russians out of the ranks of the great powers.

147
00:30:32.655 --> 00:30:51.932
[Guest] 而当你在追求这样的目标，同时又对 Russian 的基础设施造成重大破坏时，你就是在给 Russians 很强的动机，逼他们采取强硬手段，甚至可能动用核武器。
And when you are pursuing a goal like that and you're inflicting significant damage on Russian infrastructure, you're going to give the Russians. significant incentives to get tough and maybe even use nuclear weapons.

148
00:30:53.364 --> 00:31:07.364
[Guest] 我原本没想到局势会走到这一步。说实话，我自己也很惊讶，我现在竟然会说出这样的话。但我认为，绝不能低估 Ukraine 正在发生的事情，也不能低估那里的局势有多危险。还有，
I didn't think we'd be at this point. I'm actually quite surprised that I'm saying what I'm saying. But I think one does not want to underestimate what's going on in Ukraine and how dangerous that situation is. And again,

149
00:31:07.463 --> 00:31:18.663
[Guest] 回到 Middle East 的话题，我刚才提到过 Israel 可能会使用核武器。我并不是说这件事很可能发生，就像我也不是在说 Russians 很可能会使用核武器一样。
getting back to the Middle East, I was talking about the possibility that Israel might use nuclear weapons. I'm not saying that's likely any more than I'm saying that it's likely the Russians will use nuclear weapons.

150
00:31:18.814 --> 00:31:37.288
[Guest] 但你绝不能低估，一个国家在感到走投无路时会采取多么激进的行动。你完全可以设想一些合理的情境：无论是 Israelis 还是 Russians，都可能陷入绝境，并开始考虑动用核武器。
But you do not want to underestimate. The radical steps that states will take if they feel desperate. And you can hypothesize plausible situations where both the Israelis and the Russians feel desperate and think about using nuclear weapons.

151
00:31:37.387 --> 00:31:48.488
[Guest] 顺便说一句，你要明白，如果 Israel 对 Iran 使用核武器，Iran 是没有能力进行报复的。而如果 Russia 在 Ukraine 境内使用核武器，
And by the way, you want to understand that if Israel were to use nuclear weapons against Iran, Iran does not have the capability to retaliate. And if Russia were to use nuclear weapons inside of Ukraine,

152
00:31:48.788 --> 00:32:02.049
[Guest] Ukrainians 也没有能力报复。所以我们现在面对的是一个非常危险的局面。再想想我们今天这期节目里的讨论，以及你这周在其他节目里和我们同事的讨论，
the Ukrainians can't retaliate. So this is a very dangerous situation. situation that we're in. And if you think about our discussion on this show and your discussion with our colleagues and other shows that you have during the week,

153
00:32:02.150 --> 00:32:18.500
[Guest] 我觉得，大家对这些冲突接下来会走向哪里都非常悲观。我们这些人里，说实话，没人能讲出一个圆满的结局，说明这些冲突会怎么收场。而我认为，这应该让我们所有人都极其担忧。
I think everybody is very pessimistic about where all these conflicts are headed. Nobody, you know, among us can tell a happy story about how any of these conflicts end. And this, I think, should make all of us extremely worried.

154
00:32:19.539 --> 00:32:34.339
[Host] 而我们也确实很担忧。Mearsheimer 教授，非常感谢你。感谢你就这两件事——Iran 和 Ukraine——所做的精彩分析。亲爱的朋友，我们期待下周再见到你。
And worried we are. Professor Mearsheimer, thank you very much. Thanks for that extraordinary analysis on both counts, on both Iran and Ukraine. We'll look forward to seeing you next week, my dear friend.

155
00:32:34.690 --> 00:32:36.589
[Guest] 我也很期待，Judge。
I look forward to it as well, Judge.

156
00:32:36.890 --> 00:32:45.240
[Host] 谢谢。今天晚些时候，关于这一切的更多内容，一点钟播出；两点钟是金童 Max Blumenthal。
Thank you. Coming up later today at one o'clock on all of this, the golden boy, Max Blumenthal at two o'clock.

157
00:32:45.715 --> 00:33:03.965
[Host] Maco，美国军人会明知对方是无辜者还下手杀人吗？还有，三点钟，Colonel Karen Kwiatkowski 在 Judge Knapp 上发表了一篇很精彩的文章。我们是不是已经站在深渊边上了？是不是已经站在疯狂的悬崖边了？我是 Judge Napolitano，这里是 Judging Freedom。
Maco, are American troops willing to kill innocents knowingly? And at three o'clock, Colonel Karen Kwiatkowski writes a fascinating piece up at Judge Knapp. Are we on the abyss? Are we on a cliff of the insane? Judge Napolitano for judging freedom.

